<title>UK: National Power faces pension bill - paper.</title>
<headline>National Power faces pension bill - paper.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1996-12-06</dateline>
<text>
<p>British electricity generator National Power Plc could have to repay more than 200 million pounds sterling it removed from its employees' pension scheme after a landmark ruling by the Pensions Ombudsmen, the Independent newspaper said on Friday.</p>
<p>The claim follows the provisional judgment by Dr. Julian Farrand, the ombudsman, in a case brought by two National Grid pensioners.</p>
<p>Farrand said National Grid, which operates Britain's high-voltage transmission system, misused pension fund surplus cash because the scheme's rules stated the surplus could not be paid to the employer.</p>
</text>
